President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate Mark Lee Greenblatt as the Inspector General of the Department of the Interior. Greenblatt currently serves as the Assistant Inspector General for Investigations at the Department of Commerce's Office of Inspector General. He has over 15 years of oversight experience and has held various positions within the DOC OIG, U.S. Department of Justice OIG, and the U.S. Senate Permanent Subcommittee on Investigations. Greenblatt is a graduate of Duke University and Columbia University Law School. He has also served as Vice Chair of the Montgomery County Ethics Commission and was a Senior Manager in Government Fellow at Harvard University's Kennedy School of Government.

Additionally, President Trump intends to nominate Thomas A. Summers as a Member of the Board of Directors of the Defense Nuclear Facilities Safety Board. Summers previously served at the Department of Energy's National Nuclear Security Administration and retired as an officer in the U.S. Air Force. He holds a B.S. from Saint Vincent College and multiple M.S. degrees in fields such as Applied Physics, Business Administration, and National Security Strategy.